<a name="newsitem1010557332,21607,"></a>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">Gotta love patch days..</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Wednesday, January 9, 2002 by <a href="mailto:zammel@shardsofavalon.com">Zammel</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><center>Well we formed up in Kael early evening, and laid waste to King Tormax. He put out 2 Rings of Lightning for Annelia(VS) and someone else, Axe of the Kromzek Kings for Moosius's twink, Wristguard of Thunder for <b>Lemieux</b> and a head for some FT2 booties for Warz (IS).<br><br>Tormax died early and quickly, so we mosied on over to Vindicator. We had just finished CoHing some kos people when the broadcast came, Xegony down in 15 minutes!<br>So we buffed up as efficiently as possible, killed the surrounding giants, set ourselves a cleric and tank order and pulled Vindicator. He went down smoothly, with a little scare of "World Coming down, Please logout now" when he was around 25% hp. He dropped a pair of booties, which went to Poppn(IS).<br><br>Servers came down, and upon their coming back up, we logged on and whacked Vindicator again. This time he dropped a Chestplate of Vindication for .... ME!. Now not only do i have to carry around 3 breastplates, and put up with wankers asking for hammer, i have to sub in breastplates constantly! Hooray.<br><br>Statue was next on the list, and he turned out to be a quad hitter, and dropped our main tank whilst clerics stood by and laughed. We transitioned pretty nicely... our second warrior died while the clerics laughed.<br>The third tank stuck for a bit though, and then we got slow and crap in , and its kinda hard to not win from there. <br>He put out 2 Swiftblade's of Zek for Guildfunds, and a Cloak of Falling Stars for <b>Lemieux</b>.<br><br>We then raced back to Tormax, for fear of being pnp'ed, and killed him again, in an interesting fight with a bit of a skeleton crew. The fight lasted about twice as long as normal, with clerics going oom when Tormax was around 40% hp. Nevertheless, we won, and this time he put out a Horn of Hsagra for guildfund (tell me!), a head for FT2 booties for Sybian (Elp hoarder), a Crown of Kromzek Kings for Thuel (IS) - Not happy... i lost the lotto for guild looting rights, with a roll of 99 when Gathu rolled a 100 (hate you), and a Wristguard of Thunder for.... Zaing? (IS), and an axe which rotted i believe.<br><br>All in all, a fairly fun day, and get out of ntov :(<br></center></FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
