<a name="newsitem1007382201,31309,"></a>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">Test of Right Clicks.</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Monday, December 3, 2001 by <a href="mailto:zammel@shardsofavalon.com">Zammel</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><center>Many of SoA have been busy over the last few days due to the Test of Tactics 3. All in all, we had a blast. First up we faced Order of the Phoenix, from Saryrn server. We beat them flawlessly, and that was it for day 1, due to the fact ToT3 was running about 6 hours behind schedule. Fun.<br><br>Day Two saw us come up against the guild Cats in Hats, from the Drinal server. They were also beaten flawlessly, although they did not field a full 18 players. We knew our next match would be tough, as it was against the winner of the Ascending Dawn (Rallos Zek) vs Legacy of Steel (The Nameless) match. Well, Rallos beat LoS around 15-12 i believe it was, and we knew we had our toughest match yet coming up.<br><br>The Rallos fight was long, but bloody. The majority of their team had Ivandyrs Hoops, and combined with two Shadowknights, this proved to be a deadly combination. The start of the match was called, about 20 seconds later, Zasper was golem wanded 5 times, HT'ed twice and Ivandyr Hooped to hell and back. Took him approximately one second to die, he didnt even have time to click his DA idol. Nadilx followed about 4 seconds later, as their team unloaded mass charges of hoops into Nadilx, followed by Warz. Probably only 60 seconds into the match, and we were down by 3. The carnage slowed a lot as they ran out of hoop charges. Brienaire died a few minutes later, followed by a slow trickle of deaths, probably one every 3 minutes.<br><br>A little surprise that wasn't known until the start of ToT3, was that due to it being held on Rallos, debuffs did 1.5x their normal effect. This made virtually anyone rootable with Tash + Malo + Occlusion, and a rooted person is a dead person. With Zasper down so quickly, we struggled to kill any RZ players, as they were also well equipped with Soulfires and Golem Wands. We lost to the Rallos Zek team, in what was a decent game.<br><br>We had fun, and in the end, we were beaten by the better team. They were better prepared than we were, and we had virtually no hoops. Its just a shame that the tournament was so right click reliant, as right clicking DD and heal items kind of kills lots of tactics. Whoever has the most right clicks, and uses them to their maximum effect, wins.<br><br>In retrospect, myself and many others wish the ruleset was different. In all honesty, Soulfires, Hoops, Insta heal shaman potions etc should have been banned. Right click DD and heal items make PvP a very silly game. Don't get me wrong, preparation is part of any ToT, and RZ were better prepared, and better pvp'ers than we were. They deserved to win, and congratulations to them for their good tactics. <br><br>See you all for ToT4.</center><br><br><br><br></FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
<a name="newsitem1007036918,71994,"></a>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">Vulak and co</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Thursday, November 29, 2001 by <a href="mailto:zammel@shardsofavalon.com">Zammel</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><center>Another patch comes and goes, another vulak does the same. He put out a Mrylokars Dagger of Vengeance for Tass (IS), a Viik's Pauldrons of Pain for Neero (VS), and a McLear's Boots for Kohnan (VS).<br><br>King Tormax also died a swift death, and he dropped a Horn of Hsagra and a Crown for Illuminati Sancti, and a Boots of the Storm (<b>Ranum</b>) and Wristguard of Thunder(<b>Shandoa</b>) for SoA/VS.<br><br>Before the patch, we took down Vindi/Statue, which results in a vindi earring, a Breastplate of Eradication (<b>Pherawk</b>), and other crap i cant remember. We even decided to take a quick shot at The Avatar of War, for fun. We were going along nicely, but 1 minute into the fight, Sober got hit with a bad round + a bad flurry, and took nearly 6,000 damage, through defensive in one round and subsequently died.... there wasnt much hope after that. But well, it was fun, and we managed to get AoW to around 85% on our first try.<br><br>Sontalak also died somewhere along the line.<br></center></FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
<a name="newsitem1006689469,4145,"></a>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">Tunare slain!</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Sunday, November 25, 2001 by <a href="mailto:zammel@shardsofavalon.com">Zammel</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><center>In an attempt to fill the void between patch days and respawn, we decided we were bored enough to clear PoG and try Tunare. The clearing was long and boring, there are seriously too many mobs in that zone. One by one, sometimes ten by ten, the mobs fell. Sometimes it was 30 by 30, and we fell. But in the end, the zone was clear, and we buffed up for Tunare.<br><br>Our first attempt was pretty shocking. We made some strategy adjustments and vowed to stop sucking. The vow was broken on our second attempt, so we all camped and came back. The third attempt was the clincher... Tunare had 1 pixel of red left in her name, and we still managed to lose. Incredibly pissed off, we ressed in and returned with a vengeance. On our fourth shot, around 5:30am est, Tunare went down with ease. We had a total of two deaths, one being the puller, and the other being Sober. <br><br>Tunare truly is a tough, yet fun fight. She is definately one of the harder mobs in everquest at the moment, and her loot reflects this.<br><br>Sorry about the inventory stuck in the screenshots, blame Lemieux!<br><br>Tunare put out a Braid of Golden Hair for <b>Lionelies</b><br><br><img src="/news/BraidofGoldenHair.gif"><br><br>A Girdle of Living Thorns for Sitten(IS)<br><br><img src="/news/GirdleofLivingThorns.gif"><br><br>An Essence of Nature for IS (So sorry i cant remember who, been a long day!!!)<br><br><img src="/news/EssenceofNature.gif"><br><br>And an Earring of Orgasm for Sanili (VS)<br><br><img src="/news/GoldenLeafEarring.gif"><br><br>History was made, the first slaying of Tunare on Xegony.... and about the 5th in the entire everquest community. Congratulations to you all.<br></center></FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
<a name="newsitem1006431832,55401,"></a>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">Vulak times two</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Thursday, November 22, 2001 by <a href="mailto:zammel@shardsofavalon.com">Zammel</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><center>An unforeseen server crash saw us clearing NToV twice this week. Nothing unusual to report, Brienaire wasn't online to send me raunchy tells, and it all went pretty smoothly. As always, loot was plentiful, so i'll just report the Vulak drops.<br><br>First Vulak had a Hobart's Helm of War for Moosius(VS), a Kelciferous Armband of Artistry for <b> Aerylin </b> and the servers very first Yakatizma's Shield of Crafting, which went to Gathu(IS).<br><br>Second Vulak had a Ssra's Bloodstone Eyepatch, which went to IS, aswell as the servers first Abashi's Rod of Disempowerment, which went to Taehoon(IS), and the servers first Jaelin's Katana, which our very own <b>Frunkle</b> recieved.<br><br>Congratulations to all the winners.</center></FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
