<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">ELP System put in effect</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Thursday, September 20, 2001 by <a href="mailto:kellen@shardsofavalon.com">Kellen</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">As we continue to be involved in high-level encounters where a raid usually lasts for many hours, we have finally come to realized that we needed an impartial system to keep track of member participation as a direct factor in determining loot distribution.  Effective as of today, all SoA raids (whether it be a multi-guild venture or not) will be subject to the <a href="/html/elp.html">ELP Rules</a>, as determined by the officers of the guild or the raid leader.</FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
