<a name="newsitem999584413,5993,"></a>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">Bow down before your master - fear FEESH!</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Tuesday, September 4, 2001 by <a href="mailto:aedalare@shardsofavalon.com">Aedalare</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><center>First off we add a new Dragon bane to the ranks - congrats to Gradie on level 60!<br><br><img src=/news/level60.jpg></center><br><br>All the more damage to Vyemm...<br><br>Now to the true source of the update. A homage to the greatest warrior of Temple of Veeshan's north wing..  FEESH!!! Yes that's right Lord Koi'Doken, the fearsome sea monster of Norrath. I was lucky enough to capture a picture of Feesh'Doken in all his glory, and you can view this rare glimpse at the bottom of the page. First off some of you may be unfamiliar with ol' Koi.. Lets start with his melee. Goddamn this fish knows how to throw down. He can rumble with the best of them at a pace unprecedented in EQ history. We were lucky enough to have enough clerics there to keep up with his awesome damage, and a big shout out to both of them for an awesome effort! Now being a dragon Doken is also blessed with an AE. All I can say is DAMN. It's hard enough fighting a mob that hits for this much, let alone having to deal with a killer AE at the same time, and when I fail to resist it you bet your life I'll be posting here moments later to tell you just how fearsome it is!! oh yeah.. it's called Tsunami. After a long and hard fought battle we finally overcame the awesome Agent we stood against and victory was ours. Feesh, we salute you <img src=/news/icon/icon41.gif> <br><br>Now of course one must fight ones way to this awesome powerhouse who, I think all will agree, is the TRUE king of EQ. Loot has been posted here and around the place, so I'm not gonna put up links to everything we got, if you're too lazy find it yourself, that ain't my problem!<br><br>Its a little unorthodox, but this is the order they were killed - so sue me. <br><br>First up was Jorrleag (long story and really not that interesting...). Um he's kinda Vox... he has more hp.... it doesnt matter, he's dead now. Earring of Icecaster went to Gathu(IS), Helm of the Crawler went to Adante(IS) and <b>Newmoon</b> scored some silver chains.<br><br>Next up was Nev. Frankly most of us agree that Nevedaria is one of the more fun fights in EQ, and as a caster I must say its pretty funny watching all your melee turning in circles. Mask of Terror went to Endar(OOK OOK), <b>Kegwell</b> scored her Right Eye and someone else got the Medal (I'm using IS's loot list - so sue me).<br>Next up came the gimp twins. This is one place where Risk versus Reward really lives up to its potential! They dropped some shields and slashers, grats people's bank. <br><br>Zlexac. Hoshkar on steroids. It went poorly the first shot (here's a tip, if you're really hurt, and run away, the dragon will follow), but second time produced the expected result. Congrats <b>Lemieux</b> on Dragon Skin Bracer.<br><br>Aaryonar. don't ask how, don't ask why. Something went wrong the first time, and we really aren't too sure what. Bunch of linkdeaths but shouldn't have made that much difference, just seemed to stall out on him. At any rate we had a chuckle about it, pulled him and Kicked his Face in. Dropped Mask of Fall for Demincia(IS) and Gwyndor(IS) got a Katana of Pain.<br><br>Next we moved out and came in through the door, while waiting for most people to turn up cleaned Ikatiar (I was one of the people who was late, so wasn't there for the fight..), was Ikatiar - no harm no foul. Grats Thalin(IS) on Stinger, Aztek(IS) on Mask.<br><br>Eashen came next and handed over a 2 sets of Twisted Steel Gauntlets, grats <b>Zammel</b> and Zasper. <br><br>Moved in and pulled Feshlak, with both his guards, a drake and a flurrier. swish.... After rezzes we pulled Feshlak. The symmetry. The flawless execution. The perfected nuking. Yes all these things were lacking and as the screenshot shows - this is not where you are meant to have Feshlack dead. Handed over Skywatcher Monacle for Yasuki(VS) and some Boots of the Dead Dream to gn0mer_01 Zasper(IS).<br><br>Dargan. Really a wurm just doesn't belong here. A big FU for not letting me DB your sorry ass and for that robe (really.. WTF???). <br><br>Grats to Durharm(IS) and <b>Werin</b> on Wurm Claw pauldrons. Loric(IS).. I s'pose grats on robe.. I'm so sorry....<br><br>Lord Kreizen. He's like Jorrleag... but with Naggy instead of Vox. Seriously this guy is s'posed to be one of the Big 4? Give me a break this gimp isn't fit to lick the dirt off Vyemm's boots.  Grats Sitten(IS) on the Silver Disc. <b>Sober</b> and Demincia(IS) got crappy Fire Etched Flamberges. <br><br>To the other side and the fight all of us were really there for. LORD KOI'DOKEN!!! Again a massive fight. Props to the Fish. We eventually downed him. Grats <b>Walcanar</b> and Fliplotar(IS) on Helms of the Deep Sea, and Starsparkles(IS) for the SirenSong.<br><br>Lady Mirenilla. A lot of anticipation as we fronted to the last Dragon in ToV before leaveing only _THE_MAN_ and his decrepit papa left. Still went down. Still gave lewtz. <b>Shandoa</b> got the Ebony headband, Fitch(IS) got the Orb of the Crimson Bull.<br><br>Well that left North ToV pretty much empty except for Vyemm and Vulak. Today we went back to give Vyemm a few decent runs. All kidding aside I would like to say a great big GODDAMN. Full respect to LoS on the Avatar of War. That melee with that many hp? anyone that can step up to that and drop it (I dont care how you do it) deserves respect. Vyemm is a powerhouse of rage. He is angry and he wants to share with everyone. Tried a few things, unfortunately got his guards mixed up in there. Lowest we got him was about 75%. But we learnt a whole lot, and pretty sure we can fix his little red wagon soon. Time will tell. Vulak count your days, soon as your bully boy drops we gonna knock you the F*&K out.<br><br>Screenshots, um yeah - dead things:<br><a href=/news/aary2.jpg><img src=/news/TNaary2.jpg border=0 target=new></a><a href=/news/feshlak2.jpg><img src=/news/TNfeshlak2.jpg target=new border=0></a><a href=/news/feesh.jpg><img src=/news/TNfeesh.jpg target=new border=0></a><a href=/news/feeshdead.jpg><img src=/news/TNfeeshdead.jpg target=new border=0></a></FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
