<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">North Wing, a learning curve</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Wednesday, July 25, 2001 by <a href="mailto:aedalare@shardsofavalon.com">Aedalare</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">Well today we had another stab at the North Wing of Temple of Veeshan. For the past couple of weeks we have been making mild attempts to see what lay beyond our good friend Arraken, usually withmixed results. But today it came together and for the first time on Xegony Ikatiar the Venomed was slain! He was a fun fight, despite a slight hiccup at the start with agro. Congratulations to Regents (IS) on his new <b><a href=http://mmo.gameznet.com/eq/new/equipment/lazy/maskofvenom.shtml target=new>Mask of Venom</a></b> and to Marika (VS) on her, er shiney? new <b><a href=http://mmo.gameznet.com/eq/new/equipment/lazy/poisonsoakedtunic.shtml target=new>Poison Soaked Tunic</a></b>.<br><br>Along the way we also picked up a Plate Bp for <b>Ranum</b> and a Leather Tunic for <b>Werin</b>, finishing his set (leather drops are just too damn high for only two classes to use), grats!<br><br>After we had seen to Ikatiar our next stop was Eashan of the Sky. A named drake that lurks before the first dragon. We all got our first look at what lay ahead as well with out first glimpse of the ancient wyrmm Aaryonar. We couldnt get too close but i included a pic of what we did see. Our fight with Eashan was a learning experience, we had no idea what to expect or what strategy would best defeat him, but in the end despite an atrocious start we got him to some 15% health (he was at around the Eas when the last of us died). Next time he will die. At this point id like to give a hearty FU to whoever at Verant came up with those Hatchlings... very... very....... annoying. By this time it was well late in the night, and after an unfortunate accident our CR party got wiped, we decided to call it a night. We shall be returning soon to finish what we started, no doubt Eashan will be hanging at the temple pub this evening making himself sound like a big man to all his dragon mates about how he saw us off. Well you just wait buddy, you just wait.... cause your gonna get yours, you mark my words!! <br><br>Oh yeah pictures.. nothing much since lets face it we all seen Wyverns before and i didnt get a shot of Eashan (will get one next time), so i included what we saw from the main hall.<br><br><center><a href=/news/ikatiar.jpg target=new><img src=/news/ikatiarTHUMB.jpg border=0><a href=/news/aaryonar.jpg target=new><img src=/news/aaryonarTHUMB.jpg border=0> </FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
