<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">New 60, New epic. oh yeah - we smacked down Hoshkar and Xygoz too..</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Monday, July 23, 2001 by <a href="mailto:aedalare@shardsofavalon.com">Aedalare</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><center>Well first off I'll be breaking out the banner again. Congrats to <b>Tiann</b> on becoming our newest Oracle!<br>Focus plz k thxs~!<br><img src=/news/level60.jpg><p><br>Also congratulations to <b>Werin</b> on finally completing his dr00d Leaf Blower!<br><img src=/news/werinepic.jpg></center><p><br>On Saturday we headed back to Veeshan's Peak for the second time, our goal was to finally kick Hoshkar in the face enough that he fell over. Once setup and buffed we cleared out his lair, and after waiting ten minutes for him to <b>walk</b> back we got him coming, with the end result of one face-kicked dragon. Felt really good to finally see this guy go down. Congratulations to <b>Lemieux</b> and Zwei (VS) who both scored a very nice pair of <b><a href=http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/greysuedeboots.html target=new>Grey Suede Boots</a></b>, Marika (VS) on a <b><a href=http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/veldraksshortblade.html target=new>Veldrak's Shortblade</a></b> and <b>Brienaire</b> on her <b><a href=http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/shissarapothicstaff.html target=new>Shissar Apothic Staff</a></b>. We also scored a Green Scale which went to Bryden (VS) to finish up his long overdue warrior epic!<br><br>Since we didn't relly know what we were doing we spent a fair bit of time wandering and trying to figure out just what the hell we were up against hehe. So it was already well late in the day by the time we got to Xygoz. He was a total gimp and went down in no time, I think he managed to kill two people (one being me - I knew resisting silence was going to bite me in the ass).<br><br>Next up we spent some time figuring out how to get Druushk in. Thanks to a 2 hour experimentation when he actually did come people were afk and totally unprepared, leading to a spectacular opening which only got better when he agroed a nearby wurm. After cr we again had trouble pulling him, unfortunately when we did get him we tried to get our casters to dodge his AE, the result being a whole lot of dead casters and three free AE's for Druushk. By this time it was way, way too late so we left VP, but we will return armed with what we learnt this time and we expect our next trip to be <b>alot</b> smoother.<br><br>Here are some pics. I didn't have one of Hoshkar (I was dead <img src=/news/icon/icon11.gif> ) and no one sent me one (watch me get 6 in my next email check), nor a picture of Druushk, but I got a really nice one of Xygoz and included a nice landscape.<br><center><a href=/news/xygoz.jpg target=new><img src=/news/xygozTHUMB.jpg border=0></a> <a href=/news/xygozdead.jpg target=new><img src=/news/xygozdeadTHUMB border=0></a> <a href=/news/pitroom.jpg target=new><img src=/news/pitroomTHUMB.jpg border=0></a></FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
<a name="newsitem995693616,87265,"></a>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">First the preparation, then... the execution.</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Saturday, July 21, 2001 by <a href="mailto:aedalare@shardsofavalon.com">Aedalare</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">Well no update for couple days and of course it's two days where stuff happens. First up came Trakanon. Normally he'd be a total gimp and barely worth the mention, but I figure why not. Headed in at around 3am est with a grand total of 14 people from SoA and IS, 3 of them roboed. Got a few more and were sitting around in reet room after moping up protector and decided we couldn't be bothered waiting two more hours for people when we could just try now and if we failed we'd have more by the time cr was done. Well we kicked his ass. In the end I think we used a grand total of 17 actual people, the only two casualties being Sitten who got Trak-touched and me cause, well I was the only wizard casting Lure of Ice (Thxs extreme agro!). Loot was as always jaw dropping (haha). We got 6 teeth which are what we were really after, went towards finishing up some key Veeshans Peak er... keys... Also dropped <a href=http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/mannarobe.html target=new>Manna Robe</a> which went to Furzen (IS) and, since it wouldn't be Trak without one, another <a href=http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/bloodemberbreastplate.html target=new>Blood Ember Breastplate</a> which is currently sitting on Ranum's Ranadin-wanna-be sk twink. While we're at it, anyone wanna buy a BE bp? hehe.<br><br>Next day stuck with naught to do, we were going to try Dain with IS, but we had a shortage of people and no real puller so instead we decided to pay a visit everyones favorite gimp giant (no not Derekor the other one). Despite a total lack of any real effort by anyone he still dropped like the gimp he is and disgorged his usual trove of rather sad caster loot. Grats to <b>Gradie</b> on his new click toy, a <a href=http://gameznet.com/eq/equipment/vermillionorboftorrefaction.html target=new>Vermillion Orb of Torrefaction</a> and to Cyrinishad (IS) on his new <a href=http://mmo.gameznet.com/eq/new/equipment/lazy/velketorsspellbook.shtml target=new>Velketor's Spell Book</a> and <a href=http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/ss/bootsofbladecalling.jpg target=new>Boots of Bladecalling</a><br><br>Today saw us returning once again to the Halls of Phara'Dar and giving Veeshans Peak another run. We've had a slight shortage of keys lately so we needed to get a few more done, now that we have enough it's back we go. Well first up is, as always, Silverwing. As always the pull took sixty times longer than the fight. Lucky us Silverwing decided to test out her gate spell this time 'round. Hooray for camping. Only up side was she at least had the good taste to summon Frunkle, and its always funny to watch a cleric trying to melee a warrior, its just sad to have the cleric actually HURT the warrior...<br><br>At any rate after logging back in and rezzing our poor summonees (yes I know it's not a word) we went again with the predictable result of one dead dragon. Another fine display of balance and forethought from Verant, loot was as follows. Grats to <b>Zammel</b> and <b>Marlana</b> who each recieved a <a href=http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/hammerofthedragonborn.html target=new>Hammer of the Dragonborn</a>. Can someone explain to me why it wont stack with agility? Congratulations also to Norl (VS) on his uber <a href=http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/dragonclawmaingauche.html target=new>Dragon Claw Main Gauche</a> and <b>Emile</b> on his <a href=http://www.gameznet.com/eq/equipment/bluedflowerkatana.html target=new>Blue Flower Katana</a>. Thanks Silverwing, while your loot is ass, it's always a pleasure killing you.<br><br>We started late, so by this time it was already around 10:30pm but we decided to have a quick shot at Hoshkar before we logged for the night. Since this was only our second trip to VP and the first time Hoshkar handed us our ass (we were just totally unprepared for him heh) we decided to give him a whirl in safe corridor in order to see if we could get him to gate health and if we could we'd fight him in his lair. Well Hoshkar proved a total bunyip to pull. In total it took us about 45-50 minutes to get him solo. I'd like at this point to say that i have discovered the worst way to lose in EQ. It is when you <i>know</i> the mob is going to gate, but you're not sure if you can win, then winning emphatically and watching victory slip from your grasp as the dragon does exactly what you expected and gates... Being the lucky recipient of the first post-gate summon I got to watch Hoshkar with NO red left in his name summon me and kill me. he then proceeded to wipe others out one by one. By this time it was too late to actually finish him off, but you better believe we will be back there tomorrow, getting past this mofo and seeing if we can't pay a visit to a few of the other denizens of this dragon infested hovel. Tomorrow the saga continues.<br><br>Also I know it's a long ass update heh, just read what you want and gloss over the rest <img src=/news/icon/icon41.gif> <p><br><center><a href=/news/trak18.jpg target=new><img src=/news/trak18THUMB.jpg border=0></a> <a href=/news/velkdead.jpg target=new><img src=/news/velkdeadTHUMB.jpg border=0></a> <a href=/news/swdead.jpg target=new><img src=/news/swdeadTHUMB.jpg border=0></a> <br><br></FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
