<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">ToV Weekend</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Sunday, April 22, 2001 by <a href="mailto:kellen@shardsofavalon.com">Kellen</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">We set out to explore and learn how to survive in the West Wing of the Temple of Veeshan (as far as we can go anyway being KOS to everything in there and we had no mage to lug us around.) and while we did manage only to go deeper than usual on the second day, it was a good couple days overall.  There were also lots of CRs hehe, kudos to our monks and rogues for doing such a great job, once under the feet of Gozzrem, a white dragon that is probably Gorenaire's Big Daddy. <FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Wingdings">J</FONT>  <br><br><center><a href="/news/gozzrem1.jpg" target=new border=0><img src="/news/tn_gozzrem1.jpg" border=0></a> <a href="/news/gozzrem2.jpg" target=new border=0><img src="/news/tn_gozzrem2.jpg" border=0></a></center><br><br>The Gozzrem fight was fun even though we got clobbered bad. Not knowing what to expect, we charged his room and beat on him for a good minute until we got another roamer wurm.  This guy has a lot of HPs and the AE damage from him and the wurm was just too much, so we ran away like chickens back to our staging spot with Zammel, the head chicken, leading the way. <FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Wingdings">J</FONT>  <br><br>Loot was decent, we didn't get much on the first day since we just stayed at zone in but the West Wing mobs had a nice drop rate (too many wurms though). Congrats to major piece winners <b>Ceinwen</b> for Ancient Leather Tunic and <b>Nadil</b> for Ancient Silk Robe and Boots.<br><br>Other winners for those interested: <b>Julien</b>(leather boots, cap), <b>Sober</b>(plate helm), <b>Kellen</b>(plate boots), <b>Vandu</b>(silk gloves), <b>Citron</b>(chain coif), Gradie(silk gloves), Kevork-DK(leather arms), Seleron-DK(leather boots), Gininea-DK(leather boots), Megolien-DK(chain sleeves), Calren-DK(plate gloves), Wink-DK(silk sleeves, bracer), Lesbrina-DK(chain coif), Bebin-DK(chain sleeves), Dyne-DK(plate bracer), Ogarok-DK(plate bracer), Sebasttian-DK(plate gloves), Raethen-VS(silk sleeves), Frakis-VS(chain coif), and Crazdem-VS(silk sleeves).</FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
