<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">Test of Tactics II Update</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Tuesday, February 13, 2001 by <a href="mailto:kellen@shardsofavalon.com">Kellen</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">SoA/DK fielded two teams, one team led by <b>Ranum</b> (with Binnon, Zelena, <b>Calek</b>, <b>Kellen</b>, <b>Ceinwen</b>, <b>Lemieux</b> as members) and the other team led by Fuego (with Megolien, <b>Citron</b>, <b>Newlaen</b>, <b>Nadilx</b>, <b>Zerax</b>, and Balas).   Ranum&#8217;s team bowed out of the first round losing to &#8220;Havenscrubs&#8221;, however, Fuego&#8217;s team did very well advancing to the Final&#8217;s match, even beating Inner Circle&#8217;s &#8220;House of Pain&#8221; team along the way.   Fuego&#8217;s team faced off with Havenscrubs during the Finals, but the server unexpectedly went down during the battle, and was thus postponed until the Inter-Server Test of Tactics competition to be held on Feb 23-24.   Havenscrubs were ahead 3 kills to 1, but unfortunately for them, the battle will start with a clean slate to determine who will represent Xegony.<br><br>Good luck to Fuego and his team!!  You guys did our guilds proud no matter what happens. *cheers*</FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
