<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH=640 NOF=LY><TR VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><TD WIDTH=640><b><CENTER><FONT COLOR="#66FFCC" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">PLANE OF SKY RAID - A Success!</FONT></b><FONT SIZE="-2" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica"><br>Sunday, January 14, 2001 by <a href="mailto:kellen@shardsofavalon.com">Kellen</a></FONT><br><br></CENTER><FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="Tahoma,Verdana,Arial,Helvetica">Continuing on from where they left off, the SoA/DK group started the day with battling drakes and sphinxes to have a confrontation with the Sister of the Spire and ultimately the Eye of Veeshan on the topmost isle of the Plane.  The newfound knowledge and experience of battling the creatures of the lower isles have proved invaluable as it seemed almost routine when the 7th island of the Plane of Sky was cleared easily and methodically....<br><CENTER><br>The battle raged on with the Sister of the Spire.....<br><A HREF="/news/pos_sots_fight.jpg" target=new border=0><IMG SRC="/assets/images/tn_pos_sots_fight.jpg" BORDER=0></A> <A HREF="/news/pos_sots_dead.jpg" target=new border=0><IMG SRC="/news/tn_pos_sots_dead.jpg" BORDER=0></A><br><br>....and finally on to Isle 8! (seen here posing with the Eye of Veeshan and some shots of the ensuing battle)<br><br><A HREF="/news/pos_eov.jpg" target=new border=0><IMG SRC="/news/tn_pos_eov.jpg" BORDER=0></A> <A HREF="/news/pos_eov_fight.jpg" target=new border=0><IMG SRC="/assets/images/tn_pos_eov_fight.jpg" BORDER=0></A> <A HREF="/news/pos_eov_dead.jpg" target=new border=0><IMG SRC="/news/tn_pos_eov_dead.jpg" BORDER=0></A> <br><br></CENTER><br>After an arduous climb with plenty of exciting fierce battles along the way, we found ourselves victors and can claim to be one of the few guilds in the server to ever reach the top!<br><br>However, on a more somber note, a battle somewhere else would affect the end of our journey unexpectedly.   Another guild (Havenlight) had defeated the Overseer of Air in Isle 4 as we rest and recover from our battle with the Eye of Veeshan.  While we were aware that this was happening, we did not realize that the Hand of Veeshan which appears after the Overseer of Air gets killed, would attack us on sight, hence we were caught unprepared and got killed.  We did attempt to fight him again but due to lack of keys and the lateness of the hour, we were unable to do so.  Perhaps another time.....<br><br>Anyway, congratulations to SoA/DK and friends who got some nice drops and some quests completed and to those that obtained their epic quest items (which was our primary goal): <br><br><b>Ranum, Keenan</b> and Calren-DK (Spiroc Wingblade-for warrior epic)<br><b>Arbaal</b> (Blade of Abrogation-for shadowknight epic)<br>Skeep-DK (Crown of Elemental Mastery-for magician epic)<br>Fuego-DK (Cloak of Spiroc Feathers-for necromancer epic)<br>Ogarok-DK (Dagas and Spiroc Wingblade-for warrior epic)<br>Zelena-DK (Wispy Choker of Vigor and Griffon Wing Spauldors)<br><b>Calek</b> (Earthshaker&#8217;s Mantle)<br><b>Kellen</b> (Aglimente&#8217;s Flute of Flight)<br><b>Zammel</b> and <b>Marlana</b> (Sphinx-Hide Mantle)<br>Balas-DK and Damas-DK (Treant Tear)<br>and to the rest of the haste belts winners.....<br><br>GREAT JOB EVERYONE!!<br><br></FONT></TD></TR><BR><BR></TABLE>
